Response ID: resp_3706
Response Text: There are no readily available City owned venues to do any kind of festivals for 600-1000 people. Austin's old vibrant festival culture is disappearing due to a lack of innovation and prohibitive costs.
outdoor:
- The most valuable sites are farmed out to conservancies with exclusionary pricing. 
- The only urban PARD site that comes close to a festival site,  "Fiesta Gardens West End" at 2015 Jesse E. Segovia St is not available 

indoor:
- there is not a single venue in Austin other than Palmer Auditorium - a trade show site / a convention center
https://www.austintexas.gov/sites/default/files/files/Parks/Special_Events/policies/special%20event%20sites%20list.pdf

